public class Meal extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a meal in a day which can be breakfast, lunch, snack or dinner with its food list.

    • getTotalCalories

      public int getTotalCalories()
      Calculate total calories of a meal through foods. A food is made of nutrients and not nutrients. Total calories are calculated with nutrients, specifically with macronutrients that are carbohydrates, proteins or lipids.
      Returns:
      meal total calories

    • calculate

      public <T> float calculate(Class<T> myClass)
      Calculate the quantity of nutrient and not nutrient in a meal. It's based on the method in Food Class that calculates the quantity of nutrients and not nutrients in a food.
      Type Parameters:
      T - means that the method will be dealing with generic type
      Parameters:
      myClass - is a class object of a specific class type . It can be a String, an Integer or a Object
      Returns:
      nutrient or not nutrient quantity in a meal
